{
  "stem": "1581.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Number one, I was told having a baby rules us out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Number two, that my services were essential, just the same like in [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And sure enough, we were in Theresienstadt for two long years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in these two years, believe it or not, we managed to somehow build a fairly tolerable life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I got a hold of a manger-- it was kind of a part of a stable-- and there was a concrete feeding trough.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I broke this down and out of this eight by 10 room, I built a little apartment for me and my wife.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You were allowed to?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The child stayed in the children's home, and we could have access to it every day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the rules loosened up as the time went by, but Theresienstadt was by no means a pleasant, pleasant place to be.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Compared to what followed, it was extremely pleasant.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But transport after transport poured into Theresienstadt, and mostly older people came.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They came from all over Europe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They came from Holland.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They came from Belgium.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They came from Germany mainly, and they came from the rest of Europe, from France.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one day there came a Viennese transport and in it was, lo and behold, the mother of my wife, my mother-in-law.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was a very pleasant surprise, if you can name that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were extremely happy to have now both mothers with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Unfortunately, this happiness didn't last very long because invariably both old ladies were put into any transport that came up, but at that time I had good connections, and I always somehow could get them out of the transplant list until we reached October of 1943 when we were unable to get them out of it.",
      "word_count": 56
    }
  ],
